4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Henry County; to provide for the sale, use,
10 and destruction of certain abandoned, stolen, and unclaimed
11 property by the Henry County Sheriff's Office and any task
12 force of the office; and to specify requirements for the sale
13 and disposition of proceeds.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. (a) The Henry County Sheriff's Office shall
16 keep and maintain a record of all abandoned and stolen
17 personal property recovered by the sheriff's office or any
18 task force of the sheriff's office. These records shall state
19 the description of the property, the date of recovery of the
20 property, and the serial or other identifying number of the
21 property. If the property is a firearm, the records shall
22 state the description of the firearm, the date of recovery of
23 the firearm, and the serial or other identifying number, if
24 any.
25 (b) If abandoned or stolen property is sold at public
26 auction under this act, the sheriff's office shall make a
27 notation in the storage record of the sale and the amount
28 received for the property.
Page 1

received for the property.
HB203 INTRODUCED
29 (c) All records required under this act shall be open
30 to public inspection at all reasonable times.
31 (d) All abandoned or stolen property recovered by the
32 sheriff's office or task force shall be stored in a suitable
33 place to protect the property from deterioration.
34 Section 2. (a)(1) As often as necessary, the Henry
35 County Sheriff may sell at public auction, including an
36 Internet auction, to the highest bidder all abandoned or
37 stolen personal property that has been recovered under this
38 act and that has remained unclaimed by the rightful owner for
39 a period of not less than six months.
40 (2) If the abandoned or stolen property is a firearm,
41 the person holding the auction must hold a federal firearm
42 license issued by the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and
43 Explosives (ATF), and all sales involving a firearm shall meet
44 the firearm transfer requirements of federal law.
45 (b) Prior to each auction, the sheriff shall give
46 notice by publication in a newspaper of general circulation in
47 Henry County once a week for two successive weeks or by
48 posting notice in a conspicuous place at the Henry County
49 Courthouse for a period of at least 20 days. The notice shall
50 contain the place, date, and time of each auction and a
51 general description of items of personal property to be sold
52 at the auction.
53 (c) Notwithstanding subsection (b), if the abandoned or
54 stolen personal property is of a perishable nature and
55 reasonable attempts to locate and identify the owner of the
56 property are not successful, the property may be sold at once
Page 2

property are not successful, the property may be sold at once
HB203 INTRODUCED
57 without notice.
58 (d) The sheriff shall attempt to obtain the best
59 possible price for the property. The sheriff may reject any
60 and all bids if the amount bid is unreasonably low and may
61 continue the sale, from time to time, at his or her
62 discretion.
63 Section 3. (a) Prior to the sale of abandoned or stolen
64 property under this act, the owner of the property may claim
65 the property at any time by submitting sufficient proof of
66 ownership as determined by the sheriff.
67 (b) The sheriff may require the owner to pay a pro rata
68 share of the costs, if any, of publication of notice of the
69 sale of the property.
70 Section 4. (a) If abandoned or stolen property is sold
71 under this act, the proceeds of the sale shall be held in a
72 separate account for a period of six months for the owner.
73 (b) During the six-month period described in subsection
74 (a), upon demand by the owner and submission of sufficient
75 proof of ownership, the sheriff shall pay to the owner the
76 proceeds of the sale, less any cost of recovery, storage,
77 maintenance, and sale of the property.
78 (c) If the proceeds are not claimed within six months,
79 after deducting and paying all expenses incurred in the
80 recovery, storage, maintenance, and sale of the property, the
81 net proceeds shall be paid to the sheriff to be deposited into
82 the Sheriff's Fund. The funds in the account may be expended
83 at the discretion of the sheriff and shall be used solely for
84 law enforcement purposes. The receipts and expenditures of
Page 3

law enforcement purposes. The receipts and expenditures of
HB203 INTRODUCED
85 funds shall be audited by the Department of Examiners of
86 Public Accounts.
87 Section 5. Notwithstanding any other provision of this
88 act to the contrary, any abandoned or stolen firearm that has
89 been obtained by the Henry County Sheriff's Office or a task
90 force of the office and that has been unclaimed for a period
91 of six or more months, as provided in this act, may be used by
92 the Henry County Sheriff's Office at its discretion for law
93 enforcement purposes or, if unlawful or not safe for use in
94 the discretion of the sheriff, destroyed.
95 Section 6. This act applies to any abandoned or stolen
96 property held on or after May 1, 2026.
97 Section 7. This act shall become effective May 1, 2026.
